# Circulatory System

## Introduction

The circulatory system transports oxygen, nutrients, and waste materials throughout the body. It consists of the heart, blood vessels, and blood. Together, they help keep the body healthy and functioning properly.

---

## Heart

The heart is a muscular organ that pumps blood throughout the body. It has four chambers and valves that control blood flow and ensure blood moves in the correct direction.

### Four Chambers of the Heart

- Right Atrium
- Right Ventricle
- Left Atrium
- Left Ventricle

### Heart Valves

- Tricuspid Valve
- Pulmonary Valve
- Mitral Valve
- Aortic Valve

---

## Blood Vessels

Blood vessels are tubes that carry blood throughout the body.

### Types of Blood Vessels

#### Arteries
Carry blood away from the heart.

#### Veins
Carry blood back to the heart.

#### Capillaries
Tiny blood vessels where oxygen and nutrients are exchanged with body cells.

---

## Blood

Blood is a fluid that transports oxygen, nutrients, hormones, and waste products throughout the body.

### Functions of Blood

- Carries oxygen to body cells
- Delivers nutrients
- Removes waste products
- Fights infections
- Helps regulate body temperature

---

## Health Tips for a Healthy Circulatory System

- Eat healthy foods rich in fruits and vegetables.
- Exercise regularly.
- Drink plenty of water.
- Avoid smoking and tobacco products.
- Get enough sleep.
- Reduce stress.
- Maintain a healthy body weight.

---

## Summary

The circulatory system is made up of the heart, blood vessels, and blood. It helps transport oxygen and nutrients to all parts of the body and removes waste products. Healthy habits help keep the circulatory system working efficiently.
